<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Accordion on nonpunctual</title><link>https://www.nonpunctual.org/tags/accordion/</link><description>Recent content in Accordion on nonpunctual</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Fri, 01 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://www.nonpunctual.org/tags/accordion/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>10 Ragas To a Disco Beat</title><link>https://www.nonpunctual.org/posts/10-ragas-to-a-disco-beat/</link><pubDate>Fri, 01 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.nonpunctual.org/posts/10-ragas-to-a-disco-beat/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;In 1982, &lt;a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Charanjit_Singh_%28musician%29" class="external-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Charanjit Singh&lt;/a&gt; released &lt;a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Synthesizing:_Ten_Ragas_to_a_Disco_Beat" class="external-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;&amp;lsquo;Synthesizing: Ten Ragas To a Disco Beat&amp;rsquo;&lt;/a&gt; which is my favorite acid house album. (There are a lot of words in that sentence that don&amp;rsquo;t go together.) It was a marketplace flop from a musician &amp;amp; composer who otherwise had a long &amp;amp; successful career in the Indian 🇮🇳 music &amp;amp; film industries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I love talking about &lt;a href="https://www.nonpunctual.org/gear/boss-aw-3/#old-faithful" &gt;flops&lt;/a&gt;. Learning about &amp;amp; talking about &lt;a href="https://www.nonpunctual.org/gear/roland-super-jx-mks-70/#thoughts" &gt;flops&lt;/a&gt; makes me feel better. It gives me hope that so many of the things considered failures or &amp;ldquo;bad&amp;rdquo; often are really just out of phase - ahead or behind the rest of the world at the time of their release or invention.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Cordovox CL-10</title><link>https://www.nonpunctual.org/gear/cordovox-cl-10/</link><pubDate>Thu, 16 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.nonpunctual.org/gear/cordovox-cl-10/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="photos"&gt;
